# CI and sim harness

## Continuous integration

`.github/workflows/ci.yml` must run on every push/PR to `dev` and `master`:

```bash
cargo test --workspace
cargo clippy --workspace -- -D warnings
```

Optional (when fixtures exist): `cargo test -p x4mp-proto --test fixtures`

Agents must not claim workspace changes complete without these passing locally when Rust code changed.

## Sim harness (no X4 required)

Integration tests under `server/tests/` simulate fake host + client bridges (see `two_client_harness.rs`) — no X4 required.

- Fake host bridge + fake client bridge(s) over real WebSocket
- Handshake, seq ordering, broadcast, ACL rejection, reconnect replay

New replication behavior must add or extend a harness test before manual X4 smoke.

## Golden fixtures

Every event `type` in `proto/` must have `proto/tests/fixtures/<type>.json` validated by a dedicated test. See `event-protocol.mdc`.

## Chaos mode (dev only)

Bridge supports `cfg(feature = "dev-chaos")` and env vars:

- `X4MP_CHAOS_LATENCY_MS` — added RTT
- `X4MP_CHAOS_DROP_RATE` — fraction of outbound frames dropped
- `X4MP_CHAOS_DISCONNECT_AFTER` — force disconnect after N seconds

Never enable chaos features in release builds.
